President Donald J. Trump has authorized an increase in Federal funding for disaster assistance in the U.S. Virgin Islands due to the impact of Hurricane Irma and Hurricane Maria. The Federal share for relief and recovery assistance has been authorized at 90 percent, except for assistance previously approved at 100 percent. The Federal cost share for debris removal and emergency protective measures has been extended for 120 days, with the extension limited to Sheltering and Temporary Essential Power (STEP). Additionally, the Federal share for hazard mitigation measures has been authorized at 100 percent of total eligible costs. For further information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.